        <briefdescription>
<para>Generates vertex and index data for the grid geometry. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Creates a grid of vertices in the XY-plane spanning from (-1, -1) to (1, 1). Vertices are generated row by row, and indices are created to form horizontal and vertical line segments connecting adjacent vertices.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>segmentsX</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Number of subdivisions along the X-axis. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>segmentsY</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Number of subdivisions along the Y-axis.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A pair containing the vertex list and the index list for line rendering.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="exception"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>std::invalid_argument</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>If either segmentsX or segmentsY is less than 2. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
